FBIS3-32098 "drlat022_b_94011" FBIS-LAT-94-022 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Feb 1994 Inter-Caribbean Affairs Haiti Organization Claims U.S. Ambassador Fosters Communism FL0102174394 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1145 GMT 1 Feb 94 FL0102174394 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole Language: French Article Type:BFN [Text] An unknown organization has reacted following the U.S. decision to cancel the visas of Haitian Army officers. The organization, the Haitian-American League, has directly addressed Ambassador William L. Swing. The members of this league accuse the American diplomat of wanting to implement communism in Haiti.
